Mayor Stephanie M. Burke, amendment to Article 8 of the revised ordinances of the City of Medford entitled Outdoor Dining Licenses.

93
00:08:29,502 --> 00:08:42,968
Dear President De La Russo and honorable members of Medford City Council, I respectfully request and recommend that your honorable body approve the attached amendment to Article 8 of the revised ordinances of the City of Medford entitled Outdoor Dining Licenses.

94
00:08:43,508 --> 00:08:48,270
This amendment clarifies and codifies the original purpose of the Outdoor Dining License ordinance

95
00:08:48,728 --> 00:08:58,133
which is to allow for a process to review and approve the use of sidewalks and other property which is under jurisdiction of the city to be used by an appropriate entity for outdoor dining.

96
00:08:58,674 --> 00:09:04,457
In addition, it makes clear that the provisions of the ordinance do not apply to property which is privately owned.

97
00:09:04,877 --> 00:09:07,098
Of course, any rules and regulations, e.g.

98
00:09:07,158 --> 00:09:14,903
zoning, building, liquor, and health that apply to outdoor dining use on private property will remain in effect and not be altered by this amendment.

99
00:09:15,283 --> 00:09:17,444
The following is a text of the proposed amendment

100
00:09:18,070 --> 00:09:21,411
respectfully submitted yours, Stephanie Yenberg, Mayor.

101
00:09:21,431 --> 00:09:23,772
And then we have the ordinance before us.

102
00:09:24,212 --> 00:09:31,254
Before us to present tonight on the matter is the right honorable city solicitor, Mark Rumley.

103
00:09:33,034 --> 00:09:34,915
Thank you, Mr. President, members of the council.

104
00:09:34,935 --> 00:09:36,015
My name is Mark Rumley.

105
00:09:36,075 --> 00:09:38,255
I reside at 50 Woodrow Avenue in Medford.

106
00:09:38,275 --> 00:09:39,716
I'm the city solicitor.

107
00:09:40,236 --> 00:09:41,196
This is very simple.

108
00:09:42,137 --> 00:09:47,558
This amendment to this ordinance is to make clear in our outdoor dining ordinance that

109
00:09:48,258 --> 00:09:56,442
entities would have to come before the city council for their approvals if it were on city or municipal property like sidewalks.

110
00:09:56,802 --> 00:09:58,863
And that's really the only purpose here.

111
00:09:59,324 --> 00:10:12,550
Those of you who were on the council when this was initiated know that that was the tenor of our early discussions, but for whatever reason, and they're really not that important, it's been interpreted to apply even to private property.

112
00:10:13,111 --> 00:10:17,473
And so this would make it clear that private property would still have to comply

113
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:25,686
with zoning, health, et cetera, all those rules and regulations, but they would not have to come before the council for an outdoor dining license.

114
00:10:26,106 --> 00:10:28,228
So it's a matter of streamlining the process.

115
00:10:28,709 --> 00:10:38,917
